    <mj-section>
      <mj-column width="100%">
        <mj-text padding-bottom="0px">
          <h2 style="font-weight: bold">People</h2>
          <p><a href="https://www.freep.com/story/news/education/2020/04/23/detroit-schools-laptops-free-internet/3005834001/">Detroit students to get 50,000 laptops and free internet service</a><br />
            &ldquo;By early June, more than 50,000 Detroit students will have new tablet-style laptop computers with free internet access to facilitate online learning.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://medium.com/@rakyll/things-i-wished-more-developers-knew-about-databases-2d0178464f78">Things I Wished More Developers Knew About Databases</a><br />
            &ldquo;Even though it is impossible to ignore how databases work, the problems that application developers foresee and experience will often be just the tip of the iceberg.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://techcrunch.com/2020/04/24/telegram-hits-400-million-monthly-active-users/">Telegram hits 400M monthly active users</a><br />
            The <a href="https://t.me/devopsish">DevOps&rsquo;ish Telegram</a> isn&rsquo;t going anywhere. Join it and circulate news there to stay informed.</p>

          <p><a href="https://zoom.us/webinar/register/5515878238126/WN_JKysQOx_S6WqCcmRzO9rdA">CNCF Community Webinar: How to Conduct a GREAT Live Stream</a><br />
            &ldquo;This webinar is intended to show CNCF Member projects how best to use technologies like YouTube, OBS, and Twitch in order to engage their communities.&rdquo;</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2020/04/23/google-to-cut-marketing-budgets-hiring-freeze-expected.html">Google to cut marketing budgets, hiring freeze expected</a><br />
            Color me slightly nervous. Well, I&rsquo;m always nervous, that&rsquo;s the trick.</p>

          <p><a href="https://www.hanselman.com/blog/QuarantineWorkIsNotRemoteWork.aspx">Quarantine work is not Remote work</a><br />
            &ldquo;People are overwhelmed, afraid, and stressed. There&rsquo;s a background pressure - a psychic weight or stress - that is different in these times. This isn&rsquo;t a problem you can fix with a new webcam or a podcasting mic.&rdquo;</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
